  <h6>Impact Report</h6>
</div>
<div class="text-1">
  <b>Friendy</b> was born from the idea that the ability to access modern money - should be univeral.
  A homeless person asks you for some change? Do you A) Fumble in your pockets and say I left my wallet at home or B)
  sorry mate - I don't have/carry cash...
<div style="height: 20px;"></div>
  Modern financial services have reduced the ability for spontaneous philanthropy. For context, Cash Donations have reached a historic low of 7%.
  Meaning out of £5.4 Billion in donations made for 2020, only £3,780,000 were made to over
  219,000 UK homeless people.
<div style="height: 20px;"></div>
  <b>Quick maths, that's £17.26 per person - for the year.</b>
<div style="height: 20px;"></div>
  Friendy solves this by bridging the gap, using uniquely generated QR codes and your phone to donate directly to the person in front of you and <b>100%</b>
  goes to them. Now, no need to worry about saying you don't have cash, just say <b>"What's your Friendy QR code mate?</b>
<div style="height: 20px;"></div>
  Thanks,<br>
  <b>Chris and the Friendy Team.</b>
</div>
